<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-06-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="528" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Fox</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-27"><hi rend="italic">June 27,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 669.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith
                            copies, with translation, of the message<note n="1" xml:id="d528fn1">See
                                    <ref target="#pg_430">p. 430</ref>.</note> of the President of
                            Ecuador submitted to the extraordinary session of Congress, 1910. This
                            document is important, being an analysis of the position of Ecuador in
                            the present conflict with Peru.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Williams C. Fox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>